<br>
<br>
Basef on some analysis I've done, my take on multi-attacks is that it's a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>very</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> important part of our damage output with hand-to-hand.  I'm only landing 87.88% of the attacks I make in my sample, but at the same time I'm on hitting on average 1.27 times every tick (that is, every delay period.)  In fact, I'm swinging 1.45 times every tick--about equivalent to a dual-wielder attacking every other swing.<br>
<br>
Anecdotally, I had a nice little event last night where I attacked with my new proccing hand-to-hand weapons and hit three times, procced on two of those attacks (one from each weapon), and also got a critical hit in that round.<br>
<br>
The only hard question is: what do you do when the prng catches up to you and you triple miss ten times in a row.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
As for race: well, you should be able to hit the weapon speed cap of 1.5s pretty easily no matter what race if you use the savagery haste (at high levels, anyway, with good buffs).  Personally, I think that if I was trying to minmax, I'd go with a dwarf.  But then, people have theorized that quickness factors into the chance to multi-attack. <p>Harana Nyao - Guinevere - Valkyn Savage<br>
